Our Products
Discover Our Products
Alkyd Resins
An alkyd is a polyester resin modified by the addition of fatty acids and other components. Alkyds are used in paints, varnishes and in moulds for casting.
Learn More
Polyamide Resins
Synthetic polyamides are commonly used in textiles, automotive industry, carpets, kitchen utensils and sportswear due to their high durability and strength.
Learn More
Polyesters
Polyester resins are used for flat roofs, pipes, storage tanks and other waterproofing linings as well as high-specification components for the construction, marine, aerospace and automotive industries.
Learn More
Driers, Additives, Thinner
The main function is to accelerate the drying of resin (mainly alkyd) in the paint and in consequence paint film becomes hard.
Learn More
Emulsions
It has been widely used in the painting industry due to its excellent properties such as good hardness, luster, acid and alkali resistance, weather and pollution resistance, and nontoxicity.
Learn More
Blocked Catalyst
Blocked catalysts speed up the formation of polymers from the resin. They are used in gloss paints to accelerate the polymerization of the alkyd resin.
Learn More
Thermoplastic
Thermoplastic are used to make different objects such as food packaging, waterproof clothing, non-stick pots and pans, eye-wear, CDs and DVDs, cable insulation, water bottles, LCD screens, paint, furniture, toys, roofing, and medical devices.
Learn More
Thermosetting
Thermosetting are used for gas and water pipelines, automotive parts, medical equipment, construction machinery parts, signage, storage boxes, electrical plugs and casings, kitchen appliances and toys.
Learn More
Adhesives & Thickeners
Adhesives is any non-metallic substance applied to one or both surfaces of two separate items that binds them together and resists their separation
Learn More
Products Usage
What Nycil Products are used for?
Auto Finish
The substances encompass a range of products, including primers, basecoats, clearcoats, and various additives. Primers ensure adhesion to the vehicle's surface and create a smooth foundation for subsequent layers. Basecoats provide color and depth, while clearcoats offer gloss and protection
Learn More
Road Marking
What we produce are designed to withstand weather conditions, heavy traffic, and fading, while remaining clear and visible to drivers. Thermoplastic compounds are commonly used, which consist of pigments, binders, fillers, and additives.
Learn More
Floor Coating
These substances include binders, which provide adhesion and strength, and pigments, which add color and opacity. Fillers improve texture and coverage, while additives enhance properties like UV resistance, abrasion resistance, and anti-slip characteristics...
Learn More
Textile
Our chemicals for textiles encompass a wide range of substances used at various stages of textile manufacturing and processing. These chemicals serve diverse functions, from enhancing color and texture to improving durability and performance. Click the link below for more details.
Learn More
Adhesives
The chemicals we produce possess a range of properties, such as bonding strength, flexibility, and durability. Contained are specialized compounds designed to create strong and durable bonds between materials.
Learn More
Lamination & Packaging
Either solvent-based or water-based, are crucial for laminating layers of materials together, providing structural integrity and barrier properties. Barrier coatings and films are applied to prevent moisture, gases, and UV light from affecting the packaged contents
Learn More
Wood Finishes
When selecting chemicals for wood finishes, factors such as the type of wood, the desired level of protection, the intended use (interior or exterior), and the aesthetic preferences of the end user are usually considered. Our chemicals can be used in production of stains and dyes, sealers and primers, varnishes and lacquers, shellac,....
Learn More
Decorative Paints
Our chemicals are carefully formulated to elevate the visual and functional aspects of paint products. Components include pigments for color, extenders to improve coverage, binders to ensure adhesion, and thickeners for better consistency.
Learn More
Additives
From improving the lifespan of industrial coatings to optimizing the combustion efficiency of fuels, additives empowers your end products to achieve precise results. Whether it's enhancing the performance of plastics, fuels, cosmetics, or food products, additives serve as versatile tools, enabling you to unlock the full potential of your products while meeting the demands of various other applications.
Learn More

Frequently Asked Questions
Who are we?
We are the Market Leader and the largest manufacturer of synthetic resins, allied products and specialty chemicals in Nigeria.
What is the best chemical I can use for Acrylic painting?
The NYCIL AE 557 is generally suggested for all-purpose dispersion paints. It is suitable for glossy to flat, interior and exterior paints on various substrates including plaster, masonry, asbestos cement, concrete and wood. It is also an excellent binder for various types of textured finishes and surfaces.
